// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/Driver/m4_emit_mlir_rejected.test — FR-023 `-emit=mlir`
// rejection guard.
//
// **Specification anchors**:
//   - `specs/007-m4-mlir-dialect/spec.md` FR-023, SC-009 — at M4
//     the public CLI MUST reject `-emit=mlir` (the dialect is loaded
//     into the `mlir::MLIRContext` but unreachable via the driver;
//     the `Compilation::lowerToNSL` stub is reachable only from a
//     direct C++ caller). M5 will flip this to acceptance.
//   - `specs/007-m4-mlir-dialect/tasks.md` T123 (Phase 5 US3).
//
// The M3-era driver's emit-stage handler emits
// "unknown emit stage: <stage>" on stderr + the usage line and
// exits 2 for any value not in {`tokens`, `ast`} (see
// `tools/nslc/main.cpp` final fall-through branch). M4 MUST NOT add
// `mlir` to that allow-list.
//
// `not` makes lit pass when nslc exits non-zero; the FileCheck
// pipeline asserts the diagnostic text on stderr. We use `%t.nsl`
// for the input file path so the rejection occurs at argv parse
// time before any I/O — the file's contents do not matter.

// RUN: printf '' > %t.nsl
// RUN: not %nslc -emit=mlir %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// CHECK: unknown emit stage: mlir
